> What's more British than cheese and onion? Our Chef André asks. Mint and lamb, perhaps? Go on, get stuck in - and let us know what you think of it!!

Preheat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Cut the @red potato{2} in half lengthways
(no need to peel) and then chop into wedges approximately the size of your
thumb. Pop them on a #baking tray{} and drizzle with @olive oil{2%tbsp} and a
generous pinch of @salt{}. Toss well and roast on the top shelf of your oven
for ~{30%minutes}.

Cut the @red onion{1} in half through the root and peel. Thinly slice one half
into half moon shapes and chop the other half into the smallest cubes as you
can. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have
one). Finely shred the @mint{1}(leaves finely shredded).

Pop the @lamb mince{500%g} in a #mixing bowl{} and add your finely chopped
onion cubes, garlic and two-thirds of your mint leaves. Add a pinch of @salt{}
and a good grind of @ground black pepper{}. Mix everything together and shape
into equal-sized burgers.

For your salad, remove the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} and separate the
leaves. Cut the ends off the @cucumber{1}, quarter your cucumber lengthways and
then scrape out the seeds with a #spoon{}. Chop your strips of cucumber into
2cm chunks. Add your cucumber and your remaining mint to your lettuce leaves.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{90%g} and then make a dressing for your
salad. Mix the @Dijon mustard{1/2%tbsp} with the @white wine vinegar{1%tbsp}
and the @olive oil{2%tbsp} and season with a pinch of @salt{}.

Once your wedges have been cooking for ~{15%minutes}, turn them to make sure
they brown evenly, then add your sliced onion. Toss well then return the tray
to your oven for the remaining ~{15%minutes}.

Heat a #frying pan{} over high heat and add a splash of oil. When the oil is
hot, add your burgers and cook for ~{6%minutes}. Keep the heat high to make
sure they brown nicely. Turn after ~{6%minutes} and cook for ~{6%minutes} more.

> The burgers are cooked when they are no longer pink in the middle.

When your wedges are cooked, remove the tray from your oven and heat your
#grill{} to high. Slice each @brioche bun{2} in half and toast under your grill
until golden brown. Sprinkle all of your cheese on top of your wedges and pop
them under your grill. Grill for ~{2%minutes} or until your cheese is bubbling.

Toss your salad in your dressing. Put a few leaves on the bottom part of your
bun, top with a burger and then pop on the top of your bun. Serve your burger
with a generous portion of your cheese and onion wedges and some salad. Enjoy!